## Tool Selection Guidelines

### Use Midjourney For

- **Unique, creative visuals**: Hero images, future vision mockups
- **Conceptual illustrations**: Abstract concepts, transformation narratives
- **Artistic styles**: When specific artistic style is needed
- **High-quality renders**: When photorealistic or high-quality renders are needed

### Use Canva For

- **Template-based designs**: Social ad visuals, brand style options
- **Quick iterations**: When multiple variants need to be created quickly
- **Brand consistency**: When maintaining brand guidelines is important
- **Text-heavy designs**: When text and design elements need to be combined

## Quality Gates

**All visual prompts must meet quality criteria:**

- ✅ **Explicit style**: Specific style description with visual references
- ✅ **Explicit lighting**: Specific lighting description with direction and mood
- ✅ **Explicit medium**: Specific medium description with technical specifications
- ✅ **Explicit mood**: Specific mood description with emotional tone
- ✅ **2-3 variants minimum**: Each visual type has 2-3 distinct variants
- ✅ **Complete prompts**: All prompts are ready for Midjourney/Canva use
- ✅ **Platform-appropriate**: Social ad visuals are platform-specific

